The  Big  Idea 	  Speed represents how quickly an object is moving through space. Velocity is speed with a direction, making it a vector quantity. If an objects velocity changes with time, the object is said to be accelerating. As well see in the next chapters, understanding the acceleration of an object is the key to understanding its motion. We will assume constant acceleration throughout this chapter. 
